      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified-1\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/5623c260-fd6c-11e3-b84d-5254006e85c2).  Ran 10 tests.  1 tests failed: conf-sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b296cc43c469b0537bfda98fcbb05a28e277f45b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 01:12:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/259811c6-fd96-11e3-a01a-5254006e85c2).  Ran 21 tests.  1 tests failed: sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "40d1946a864a89284aec4525b7ccf8edb48be708",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 19:48:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nChris, in your comment when you write about \"semantic changes introduced in LU-5259\" do you really mean \"semantic changes introduced in LU-5073\"?\n\nI definitely agree that having more documentation is always good, and we have started adding descriptive comment blocks to code under LU-4974, LU-4975, LU-4976 and other patches that are adding or making major changes to functions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ea48bf2c799a2cd115b69cbc5e980353eee39436",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 19:55:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAh yes, I meant LU-5073",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bce84527af6c97fedd7a6097077c7b8ee9867d30",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 20:10:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAnd yeah, code comments are great, but it's event better if the usage of functions is semantically consistent. As an example, in ptlrpc_unregister_reply() we have the following usage and associated comment:\n\n        if (!ptlrpc_client_recv_or_unlink(request))\n                RETURN(1);\n\n        /*\n         * Move to \"Unregistering\" phase as reply was not unlinked yet.\n         */\n        ptlrpc_rqphase_move(request, RQ_PHASE_UNREGISTERING);\n\nThe \"as reply was not unlinked yet\" is no longer an accurate statement with LU-5073",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c3f5b84dccecdec3e0a4a877b1ec4e19f1dc3050",
      "author": {
